<section class="section-shell py-24">
  <div class="text-center mb-12">
    <p class="section-kicker mb-3">Theoretical framework</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">
      Economic Justification
    </h2>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <article class="glass-card p-7 md:p-8">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">
        Market Structure
      </h3>
      <p class="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
        The lifestyle footwear market displays monopolistic competition.
        Multiple firms compete in the same category, including Nike, Puma,
        New Balance, Converse, and Adidas. Even with many competitors, each
        brand keeps some pricing power through product differentiation in
        design, perceived quality, and emotional positioning. Adidas does not
        fully control prices, but it can influence them through brand identity.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="glass-card p-7 md:p-8">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">
        Demand Elasticity
      </h3>
      <p class="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
        Demand for Adidas Samba is relatively elastic because buyers can switch
        to similar alternatives. However, strong model differentiation and
        social-media hype make demand more inelastic than generic sneakers.
        Consumers perceive additional symbolic value that lowers price
        sensitivity.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="glass-card p-7 md:p-8">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">
        Entry Barriers
      </h3>
      <p class="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
        Production barriers are moderate, since manufacturing footwear is not an
        impossible technical challenge. The high barrier appears in building
        global recognition, reputation, and brand loyalty. The true advantage
        is not simply producing sneakers, but making consumers desire them.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="glass-card p-7 md:p-8">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3 text-white">
        Positioning Strategy
      </h3>
      <p class="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
        Adidas reinforces its position through digital marketing, collaborations
        with celebrities and influencers, and continuous visibility on
        platforms such as Instagram and TikTok. This builds aspirational
        perception and strengthens brand loyalty, helping sustain above-average
        prices.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
